What a Product Director answer sounds like

> My first priority would be establishing facts.

I would immediately engage engineering, SRE, and operations teams to determine whether the outage originated within our platform, identify the affected APIs, and estimate the scope of customer impact.

While engineering is working on restoration, I would establish a communication cadence with the fintech partner. Even if we don't yet know the root cause, I want them hearing updates directly from us rather than discovering issues themselves.

Once service is stabilized, I would assess customer impact: how many API calls failed, which customer journeys were affected, and whether any regulatory or contractual obligations were triggered.

I would then coordinate with legal, risk, and communications teams if the incident met escalation thresholds.

Finally, after recovery, I would lead a postmortem focused on root cause, prevention measures, and resilience improvements so that both our teams and our partners have confidence that the issue will not recur.

In Open Banking, reliability is part of the product. Customers may never see the API, but they experience every outage.



Notice the structure:

